</h2>
<h3>
    <strong>Geography and River Systems</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    Eugene is nestled between the Cascade Mountains and Oregon's rugged coast, giving anglers easy access to diverse river systems. The Willamette, McKenzie, and Siuslaw Rivers are prime habitats for winter steelhead thanks to their clean, cold waters and natural spawning grounds.
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>Seasonal Patterns and Migration Cycles</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    Steelhead begin migrating into these rivers during the late fall, peaking in numbers from December to March. Unlike salmon, steelhead often survive spawning and may return to the ocean—a behavior that shapes their unique and elusive nature.
</p>
