<h2>
    <strong>Effective Fishing Techniques for Winter Steelhead</strong>
</h2>
<h3>
    <strong>Drift Fishing</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    A time-tested method using bait (roe or shrimp) drifted naturally along the bottom. Works best in deeper pools and tailouts.
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>Float Fishing</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    Keeps bait suspended and visible in the strike zone. Ideal for slower runs and deep eddies.
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>Fly Fishing</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    Use weighted nymphs, egg patterns, or spey setups. Effective in clear, low water where subtle presentation matters.
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>Spin Fishing</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    Spinners and spoons like Blue Fox or Little Cleo excel in turbulent water, enticing aggressive strikes.
</p>
